on a scale to put the suffering that occurred as a result of the Ã¢â‚¬Å“ethnic cleansingsÃ¢â‚¬ï¿½ in the former Yugoslavia in the 1990s in the shade. They took place without any attempt at concealment, under the eyes of tens of thousands of journalists, diplomats, relief workers, and other observers with access to modern communications, in the middle of the worldÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s most crowded continent. Yet they aroused little attention at the time. Today, outside Germany, they are almost completely unknown.
